## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-103">SQL Server 的.NET Framework 数据提供程序遇到服务器生成的错误时，会创建此类。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-103">This class is created whenever the .NET Framework Data Provider for SQL Server encounters an error generated from the server.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-104">（客户端错误引发作为标准公共语言运行时异常。）<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException>始终包含至少一个实例的<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlError>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-104">(Client side errors are thrown as standard common language runtime exceptions.) <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException> always contains at least one instance of <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlError>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-105">严重性级别为 10 或更少的消息是信息性消息，并指示由用户输入的信息中的错误导致的问题。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-105">Messages that have a severity level of 10 or less are informational and indicate problems caused by mistakes in information that a user has entered.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-106">严重级别为 11 到 16 生成的用户，并可以由用户纠正。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-106">Severity levels from 11 through 16 are generated by the user, and can be corrected by the user.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-107">严重级别为 17 到 25 的消息指示存在软件或硬件错误。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-107">Severity levels from 17 through 25 indicate software or hardware errors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-108">当级别为 17 时、 18 或 19 的错误时，您可以继续工作，尽管您可能不能够执行特定语句。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-108">When a level 17, 18, or 19 error occurs, you can continue working, although you might not be able to execute a particular statement.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-109">当严重级别为 19 或以下时，<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection> 将保持打开状态。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-109">The <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection> remains open when the severity level is 19 or less.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-110">20 或更高版本的严重级别时，服务器通常会关闭<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-110">When the severity level is 20 or greater, the server ordinarily closes the <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-111">但是，用户可以重新打开连接并继续操作。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-111">However, the user can reopen the connection and continue.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-112">最后两种情况下，执行该命令的方法将生成 <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-112">In both cases, a <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException> is generated by the method executing the command.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-113">有关 SQL Server 发送的警告和信息性消息的信息，请参阅[数据库引擎错事件和错误](/sql/relational-databases/errors-events/database-engine-events-and-errors)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-113">For information about the warning and informational messages sent by SQL Server, see [Database Engine Events and Errors](/sql/relational-databases/errors-events/database-engine-events-and-errors).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-114"><xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException>类映射到 SQL Server 严重级别。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-114">The <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException> class maps to SQL Server severity.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-115">下面是处理异常的常规信息。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-115">The following is general information on handling exceptions.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-116">你的代码应捕获异常来阻止应用程序崩溃并允许向用户显示一条相关的错误消息。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-116">Your code should catch exceptions to prevent the application from crashing and to allow displaying a relevant error message to the user.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-117">可以使用数据库事务来确保数据的一致性，而不考虑客户端应用程序 （包括故障） 中会发生什么情况。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-117">You can use database transactions to ensure that the data is consistent regardless of what happens in the client application (including a crash).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-118">System.Transaction.TransactionScope 或 BeginTransaction 方法 （在 System.Data.OleDb.OleDbConnection、 System.Data.ODBC.ODBCConnection 和 System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection） 等功能确保一致的数据，而不考虑异常引发由提供程序。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-118">Features like System.Transaction.TransactionScope or the BeginTransaction method (in System.Data.OleDb.OleDbConnection, System.Data.ODBC.ODBCConnection, and System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection) ensure consistent data regardless of exceptions raised by a provider.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-119">事务可以失败，因此捕获失败和重试该事务。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-119">Transactions can fail, so catch failures and retry the transaction.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-120">请注意从.NET Framework 4.5<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException>可以返回一个内部<xref:System.ComponentModel.Win32Exception>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-120">Note that beginning with  .NET Framework 4.5, <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException> can return an inner <xref:System.ComponentModel.Win32Exception>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-121">异常类的.Net Framework 数据提供程序报告特定于提供程序的错误。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-121">The exception class of a .Net Framework data provider reports provider-specific errors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-122">例如 System.Data.Odbc 具有 OdbcException、 和 System.Data.OleDb OleDbException，并 System.Data.SqlClient 具有 SqlException。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-122">For example System.Data.Odbc has OdbcException, System.Data.OleDb has OleDbException, and System.Data.SqlClient has SqlException.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-123">错误详细信息的最佳级别，捕获这些异常并使用这些异常类的成员获取错误的详细信息。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-123">For the best level of error detail, catch these exceptions and use the members of these exception classes to get details of the error.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-124">除了特定于提供程序的错误，.NET Framework 数据提供程序类型可以引发 System.OutOfMemoryException 和 System.Threading.ThreadAbortException 等的.NET Framework 异常。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-124">In addition to the provider-specific errors, .NET Framework data provider types can raise .NET Framework exceptions such as System.OutOfMemoryException and System.Threading.ThreadAbortException.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-125">可能无法从这些异常中的恢复。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-125">Recovery from these exceptions may not be possible.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-126">输入错误可能会导致引发 System.ArgumentException 或 System.IndexOutOfRangeException 等异常在.NET Framework 数据提供程序类型。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-126">Bad input can cause a .NET Framework data provider type to raise an exception such as System.ArgumentException or System.IndexOutOfRangeException.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-127">在错误时调用的方法可以引发 System.InvalidOperationException。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-127">Calling a method at the wrong time can raise System.InvalidOperationException.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-128">因此，一般情况下，编写异常处理程序捕获任何提供程序的特定异常，以及从公共语言运行时异常。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-128">So, in general, write an exception handler that catches any provider specific exceptions as well as exceptions from the common language runtime.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-129">这些都可以按如下所示进行分层：</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-129">These can be layered as follows:</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
try {  
   // code here  
}  
catch (SqlException odbcEx) {  
   // Handle more specific SqlException exception here.  
}  
catch (Exception ex) {  
   // Handle generic ones here.  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-130">或：</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-130">Or:</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
try {  
   // code here  
}  
catch (Exception ex) {  
   if (ex is SqlException) {  
      // Handle more specific SqlException exception here.  
   }  
   else {  
      // Handle generic ones here.  
   }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-131">还有可能无法在堆栈上没有用户代码使用线程池线程上的.NET Framework 数据提供程序方法调用的。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-131">It is also possible for a .NET Framework data provider method call to fail on a thread pool thread with no user code on the stack.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ae8b0-132">在这种情况下，并使用异步方法调用时，必须注册<xref:System.AppDomain.UnhandledException>要处理这些异常，并避免应用程序故障事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ae8b0-132">In this case, and when using asynchronous method calls, you must register the <xref:System.AppDomain.UnhandledException> event to handle those exceptions and avoid application crash.</span></span>  
  
   
  
